Final notes
***********

   MailArchiver is written in C language, and was developped on an
Amiga 3000 UNIX-1 (10 Mb RAM, internal HD disk drive, two internal hard
disks of 100 Mb and 160Mb, external SyQuest drive of 88 Mb, external
floppy disk drive, 1960 monitor and Star LC24-10 printer) connected by
a null-modem cable to an A500 with 1 Mb RAM.

   The core of MailArchiver was written using a few spare time I had in
the last days of 1993. For the first time of my life, I used the
@{b}gadtools.library@{ub} for the GUI, and @{b}TeXInfo/MakeGuide@{ub} for the
documentation.

   MailArchiver is dedicated to Michel Schinz, whithout whom I wouldn't
have an electronic address. Thanks to you Michel !


@EndNode

